- Oh, we‚Äôve finally finished studying! Congratulations! 
- Yeah, exactly! It‚Äôs such a weird feeling not to be a senior anymore. And what are you going to do after it?
- To be honest, I have hardly had time for myself lately.  I buried myself in books and paid almost no attention to anything around me.  it has been a very difficult year for me, so I want to give myself a few months off. 
 - what are you going to do during this time period? 
- saying so , I don't mean that I will lie on the couch and watch TV shows all these months, I want to prepare myself for the further stages of my life.  first of all, I want to take additional courses in programming or an internship at some IT company in order to gain practical skills in my professional field.  in parallel, I want to sign up to self-development courses that will help me with such things?  as: .resilience,  stress-tolerance, motivation, how not to stuck in a rut and team communication .  I also want to pick up the??? English language. I hope , I will be able to go to America for a month according to the program 
" work and travel ".
- Why don't you just get a job and do all your plans while working ? 

- I need such period of time, because if I start working on a full-time job, I will quickly burn out  and become very exhausted and unproductive. But completing the plan mentioned before, will save me from that. 

- Woah, wonderful! It sounds like a perfect plan! I agree, sometimes you just need to have a rest, but I think operating conditions influence your mental state a lot, too. In what conditions would you like to work?

- probably these days it sounds strange, but I want to be an office clerk in an international company :) white-collar jobs attracts with the possibility of career growth, stability and comfortable working conditions.  I also really like the remote work option.  Each of these types of work has its own pros and cons, so my ideal option is a mixed type of work.  I like the prospect of working in a well-paid job with a stable nine-to-five work schedule.  it is important for me to be confident in the future, which I cannot feel  working as a freelancer or being self-employed.  just imagine: you can confidently climb the career ladder without (overworking) or harming your mental and physical health.  at any moment you can take some things necessary for working process and go somewhere to the sea to work remotely from there.  it seems to me being in such a living environment rises sence of self-worth and the enjoyment of life

- I hope your dreams will become true! 

- thanks. What about you? Have you already chosen the field you want to work in?

- Yep, I have. I want to become a Data scientist programmer.

- wow ! Sounds cool ! Why have you chosen such profession ? 

- Well, you know‚Ä¶ I‚Äôve chosen this job because, firstly, I‚Äôve got a Bachelor Degree in Applied Math and I want to use that knowledge I‚Äôve been imbibing for 4 years, and, secondly, programming develops creativity, critical thinking and problem solving skills. Also it teaches you to gain patience and persistence and, you know, programming can be applied in almost every field! So you get much more opportunities and freedom. Well, and I really need to mention programmes‚Äô earnings - it is much higher than other career fields. So basically, I expect this job to develop my personality, make my mental health more stable and handle my financial needs.

- I Absolutely agree with you ! Do you think this kind of work can help the world to become a better place ?

- I think that being a programmer is that job which can help the world become better for sure! Just imagine: storing information, carrying out transactions and having access to databases can save someone's lives! Who knows, maybe one of us will develop a device for visually impaired people soon, and another might bring up the predictive model to prevent future famine. Situations with poor countries worsen, the climate changes faster, people with special needs feel oppressed. There are so many unsolved problems that every try deserves attention.

–ú–∞—à, –∞ —Ç–≤–æ—î prev job —Ü–µ what did you like or dislike about your previous job ?

-... So tell me please about your previous positions. Why did you resign from yoir job? 

- Well, I've been working in Gamedev company for quite long time, and then dropped out, because it honestly was just the dead-end job, we haven't created a worthy product in a while. I then joined Black Wing Foundation, and I often was underpaid there, so I decided to quit, too. Now I'm freelancer already for 5 month.

- What about your education? Have you graduated from university? And what have you been majoring in? 

- Yes, I have a Bachelor of Arts. I've got my degree from the Academy of Fine Arts, where I've spent one year in Poland, I went there as an exchange student. And also I've completed a Graphic Design course and Virtual Reality course.

- What are you looking for in a job? 

- I expect the job that will make me better and allow to work hard. I am ready to heavy workload and I hope this job will force me to learn how to cope with difficult situations.

-...... Tell me a little about yourself. 

- Okay, so, I have a strong experience in Adobe Illustrator and Photoshop and am working with vector based graphic design. I have a great eye for light, composition, colour, staging, architecture and a full understanding of human anatomy, shape language and silhouette. Also I'm interested in science and materials and able to work in many different art styles. 
If we talk about soft skills, I'm a strong conceptual thinker and have a passion for storytelling. I also have an experience dealing directly with clients. My communication skills are really good! I can get along with very picky client. And I'm able to learn fast!

- Salary

- My salary range is flexible, but I have significant experience in this field and lots of needed skills, I think this adds value to my candidacy. I look forward to discussing in more detail what my responsibilities would be, so we can determine a fair salary for my position. 

- Portfolio 

- Sure! Here it is

- Good morning! I'm Masha, nice to meet you. We've seen each other earlier today. So, I've read your CV and now I have a couple of questions. Are you ready to start? 
-
- Okay, now tell me about yourself, please.
-
- Aha.... Good. And what are your greatest strengths?
-
- Alright, thanks.. Tell me please now, why did you resign from your job? 
-
- Yeah, I see. And why do you want to work with us?
-
- Great! Now, why should we hire you? 
- 
- Thank you, Maria. Now, I'll ventilate certain points. So, you will have to work nine to five, the schedule will be hectic. Also there's an ability to take additional hours and work overtime, so you'll be paid more, you'll get salary twice a month. Be ready to manage unknowns! And now, do you have any questions? Is there anything else you'd like to know? 
-
- Honestly, we don't support working from home, but it can be possible. As you will be provided with all needed equipment, it can be organised easily, but be sure to implement a plan in time. 
-
- Well, then I'm going to contact you this evening in any case. Thank you!
